1. Start Trivia Game
Task A: Create start button    (2)
Create a GUI to allow player to click button on android app that says something like "start game".
Task B: Add design to interface  (1)
Write code to add colors and change font for button.
Task C: Code where buttons takes user (2)
Code function to direct button "onclick" to first question. 

2. Format trivia questions
Task A: Create API  (5)
Decide what questions game will use from open trivia DB
Task B: Integrate API   (5)
Code API data into android application main activity
Task C: Format questions   (3)
Format question and multiple choice answers on display
Task D: Add buttons  (1)
Add buttons to answers for user to click choice

3. Pop-up Correct/Incorrect
Task A: Pop-up for correct answers  (3)
Use snackbar function for pop-up message saying user chose correct answers, this function returns 1 for scoreboard counter. 
Task B: Pop-up for incorrect answers  (1)
Use snackbar function for pop-up message saying user chose incorrect answers, this function returns 0 for scoreboard counter. 
Task C: Code button for correct answer (2)
Add code to button for correct answer to call snackbar function for pop-up saying "correct". 
Task D: Code button for incorrect answer  (2)
Add code to button for incorrect answers to call snackbar function for pop-up saying "incorrect".

4. Scoreboard
Task A: Create counter function (3)
Create function that accepts parameter of each question's score (0 or 1) and returns summed score. 
Task B: Create scoreboard  (3)
Create textbox on display that displays summed score returned from Task A's function. 
Task C: Format scoreboard (1)
Format scoreboard so it is in bottom right corner. 


